### canPipelineLoop() {#a8bf297083af7778a3578982d027c7194}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool MachinePipeliner::canPipelineLoop (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineloop">MachineLoop</a> &amp; L)</>}>
Return true if the loop can be software pipelined.

The algorithm is restricted to loops with a single basic block. Make sure that the branch in the loop can be analyzed.

### scheduleLoop() {#a280d29b722d6aeaf32d002d228fe712e}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool MachinePipeliner::scheduleLoop (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineloop">MachineLoop</a> &amp; L)</>}>
Attempt to perform the SMS algorithm on the specified loop.

This function is the main entry point for the algorithm. The function identifies candidate loops, calculates the minimum initiation interval, and attempts to schedule the loop.

### swingModuloScheduler() {#ab2e852fbfde7fffa945306fefad06fd3}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bool MachinePipeliner::swingModuloScheduler (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machineloop">MachineLoop</a> &amp; L)</>}>
The SMS algorithm consists of the following main steps:

<ul>
<li>Computation and analysis of the dependence graph.</li>
<li>Ordering of the nodes (instructions).</li>
<li>Attempt to Schedule the loop.</li>
</ul>

Declaration at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/machinepipeliner-h/#l00111">111</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/codegen/machinepipeliner-h">MachinePipeliner.h</a>, definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/machinepipeliner-cpp/#l00470">470</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/codegen/machinepipeliner-cpp">MachinePipeliner.cpp</a>.
